Nigella Lawson's ban from the US could have a huge impact on the future of her ABC show, The Taste.

The curvaceous British TV chef, 54, who was refused entry to America because of her court confession that she took coke, has been a judge on the reality show for two seasons.

However, today, an ABC source told MailOnline: 'No decision has been made yet on whether or not the show will come back for a third season. 

'We finished production on season two ages ago and the finale episode aired in February.'

